**Video explanation:** https://youtu.be/utGtzLNMu0I
------------------------------------------------------------------
This is aimed at **advanced users** that want to enhance their experience, **NOT **for complete beginners.
**Basic AddOn, ElvUI and WeakAura knowledge and is REQUIRED**
**Never update weakauras via the weakaura companion.**
When there is a new version of the UI available, you will be notified in respective **changelog **channel. 
------------------------------------------------------------------
**Installing/Updating the UI via clean installation**

**Disclaimer** 
By following this method, your current UI will be wiped clean, so make sure to have a copy somewhere if you want. 
```Step 1: Exit game.
Step 2: Download the NaowhUI Installer + Addons. You will need a rar software (Winrar, Winzip, or 7zip) to extract the files.
Step 3: Find your WoW directory (Usually found in local disk C:/program Files(x86)/WorldofWarcraft). Make a backup of your WTF folder, then delete both WTF and Addons folders.
Step 4: Open the NaowhUI folder you downloaded and copy the Interface folder to your WoW directory. 
Step 5: Update your addons with Curseforge. (ElvUI is not supported by Curseforge, so get wowup or tukui client for ElvUI)
Step 6: Open the game, make sure all addons are enabled. The installer should automatically pop up, if not type in /naowhui in chat.
Step 7: Follow the instructions on Installer. The game will reload, and your UI will look fine. 
Step 8: Close the game and go to your old WTF back up folder. Find the "Config" file and copy it in your new WTF folder to get your old graphic and sound settings restored.```
**Installing/Updating the UI via import strings (Does not support all addons)**

```Step 1: Exit game.
Step 2: Update your addons with Curseforge. (ElvUI is not supported by Curseforge, so get wowup or tukui client for ElvUI)
Step 3: Open the game, and import the profile string to the addon you want to update (ElvUI, WA, Details, ...).
```

**Plater NPC color guide **
```Dark Blue: Important mob (Frontals/Big Damage Mob)
Teal: Caster/Healer mob (Interrupt)
Pink: Second caster/important mob
Purple: Main target in pulls
Orange: Tanked by Treants/Earth Elemental Totem```

**How to disable/enable Blizzard Class Spell Proc indicator (The shiny stuff around your character for procs like Rime(DK) or Hot Streak(Mage))**
```Go to ESC -> Settings -> Gameplay -> Combat -> Set "Spell Alert Opacity" to 100%. Then:
- If you are on a Druid, Shaman, or Evoker type /console displaySpellActivationOverlays 0
- If you are on any other class type /console displaySpellActivationOverlays 1```

**How to Install SharedMedia <Naowh>**
```
1] Delete "SharedMedia" & "SharedMedia_MyMedia" folders in your Interface/AddOns folder
2] Add "SharedMedia_Naowh" folder to your Interface/AddOns folder, Download link can be found in #naowhui-retail
3] Update your plater profile so the target arrows will work and don't show green boxes.
```

**Buffs are colored squares instead of icon of the spell/buff**

```/ec -> Unitframes » Group Units » Aura Indicator » Configure Auras » Select the spell you want to change » Style » Textured Icon » Then change the size and where it should be placed on your party frames```

** How to get Cyrillic Naowh font working on english realms:**
1. First finish the normal UI install flow, NaowhUI installation + SharedMedia_Naowh folder..
2. Go to your "_ Retail " folder and paste this font folder in it.
3. Restart the game

**A few words regarding the m+ WA packs (huge packs!):**

```- You should **avoid** being in Valdrakken -> the city is a lagfest, dont recommend doing it there
- Having an SSD is highly recommended (its even a requirement for the base Game itself)
- When you copy the import string and hit import, GO AFK. Literally. Don't touch your game at all, let the import finish. **DO NOT close the panel** until its done or you will have issue. (Obviously DONT WAIT 30mins, this cant take more than 1 minute.)
^- after this, close the WA panel and do a reload.
- DO NOT import the pack during a dungeon.
- Disable all your addons BUT weakauras (obviously) when you are importing the pack.
^-do this last one ONLY if you have troubles importing big WA packs or if you know your PC is a lower-end one.

- editing the pack: if your PC is struggling with the whole group, click on the "+" sign and edit/move the stuff there individually, or in smaller groups

Following these the import should work with other stuff not breaking.
If it still doesn't work and you did everything humanly possible to make it work then let me know.```

**How to change the length of the Names on Unitframes:**

You have to go to Elvui -> Unitframes -> then navigate to whichever unitframe you want to change.
__Example__: Elvui -> Unitframes -> Individual Units -> Player -> **NAME**

Now when you are there, you select whichever Tag your prefer from the "Available Tags" elvui tab (attached pic.) and replace the "Text format" with that.

**OmniCD in Raid and how to move them:**

You can see 3 things with Naowh's OmniCD profile:

1: **External defensive CDs** available by your healers
(you can move them by going into omnicd - Raids - Extra bars -  "1" - untick "lock frame" then move it)

2: **External offensive CDs** available
(you can move these by going into omnicd - Raids - Extra bars -  "2" - untick "lock frame" then move it)

3: **Racials**, such as Will of the Forsaken (Undead), Will to Survive (Human) etc. 
If you dont want to see them, go to Raids - Spells - Racial traits - untick them

**OmniCD in Dungeons and how to move them:**

1: **External defensive CDs** available by your healer
(you can move them by going into Omnicd - Dungeons- Extra bars -  "1" - untick "lock frame" then move it)

2:  **Offensive CDs**, they are anchored to the right side of your party frame.
You can set what spell you want to track by going into Dungeons - spells -> select the class then tick whatever you want 

3:  **Group CCs available **
(you can move them by going into Omnicd - Dungeons- Extra bars -  "2" - untick "lock frame" then move it)

4: **Other stuff** (such as Immunities, priest grips, etc.) not visible on this picture (these are next to your Details windown on the bottom right)
(you can move them by going into Omnicd - Dungeons- Extra bars -  "3" - untick "lock frame" then move it)

5: **Interrupt bar** (**updated position: left of the Group CCs**)
(you can move it by going into Omnicd - Dungeons- Extra bars -  Interrupt Bar - untick "lock frame" then move it)

**Sounds in M+ Dungeons**

It's not Bigwigs or Littlewigs. The sounds are from the m+ weakaura in <#1138380698143698954>  - Generic Weakauras

**Show my spells and interrupts in OmniCD**
```Open /omnicd and make sure "Show Player" is checked```

**How to add Raid group number to your player frame:**

```I've seen this question asked several times now so here we go:
1. Open Elvui -> Unitframes -> Individual Units -> Player -> Custom Texts
2. type anything under "Create Custom Text" , then hit Okay on the right side
3. "Text Format" must be [group:raid], rest of the settings you modify however you want (you can copy my setting from the screenshot below as reference)
4. Congrats! You are done.```

**Show Nameplate of Afflicted Mob**

```You need to enable these Options (in Blizzard Options Menu) to see the Nameplate of the Afflicted mobs.
You ALSO need to uncheck "Hide Blizzard Health Bars" in Plater options! 
We are still working on a better solution. But that's the way it works now.```

**To get (or to Uninstall) the Elvui-styled login screen/character screen:**

Adding the zip here, as Tukui website ~~||went poo poo||~~ got redesigned for whatever reason and their forums is also not available.
Installation instructions are in the README file by them.

**Uninstalling:** simply remove every folder from your retail\Interface folder BUT keep: **AddOns, Tooltips, ICONS**
⚠️  (IF YOU REMOVE THESE **THREE** AS WELL YOU WILL BASICALLY DELETE YOUR ADDONS, CHAT BUBBLE FILES, AND THE CUSTOM ICON PACK) ⚠️ 

https://github.com/Tiifs/elvui_login_screen_and_character_selection

**How to edit the Plater color mod so you can see your very own stuff?**

Its the AuraNameplateColors-v3 Mod from Plater that changes your Nameplates Colors with different debuffs applied.

Follow these steps and it will make our lives super easy and fun!

```1. Open plater (/plater)
2. Navigate yourself to the "Modding" tab
3. Click on "AuraNameplateColors-v3" , then click on "Constructor"
4. Add your own stuff as shown in the example on the screenshot
  - if you don't know how to copy paste, then please type what you can see on the screenshot
- You have to change the debuff ID (in green) and the color code (in yellow) yourself
- Debuff ID you can get by moving your mouse over the DEBUFF on an enemy unitframe
- Color code you can get multiple ways, the easiest is probably using this site: https://www.colorhexmap.com/50e2f2
6. CLICK SAVE for the love of God, or your changes will be lost and you'll have to start over!
7. By normal behavior it will now work on your next debuff application. If for some reason it doesn't, /reload and try again
    - if after this it still doesn't work, then you messed something up. Either missing a letter, a number, or a symbol, so check what you wrote and correct it!
8. Congrats, you are done!```

# How to reset your user interface
*There are many ways to achieve this, but this one is non reversible and will nuke EVERYTHING*

To ensure this works, please follow each step precisely and in order

1) Log into a character
2) Disable all AddOns while staying logged in
3) Go to ESC -> Options and click on the "Defaults" button, pick "All Settings"  or similar, forgot the exact naming
4) Right click on the General Tab of your chat and click on "Chat defaults"

5) Logout of your character, DO NOT close the game

6) Log back into your character, the reason you have to log out once is to make cvars reload
7) Type the following into your ingame chat `/console cvar_default`
8) Close the game

9) Delete **EVERY single folder** inside your wow _retail_ directory **BUT** "Utils", do not touch any files that are not folders

Now you can proceed with a clean installation

**New Installation is not working properly**

```Make sure you deleted NaowhUi_installer inside your Addons folder. It's not needed anymore. The new one is called NaowhUi

To trigger the Installation again, go into Elvui Options 
(/ec) and press the big NaowhUi Button. 

!/naowhui is gone and not working anymore!```

**Help! <#1138380698143698954> is empty**
```Enable the correct Discord settings. 
Go to Settings > Text and Images > Make sure "Embeds and link previews" is enabled.```

**Chatbubble variants:**

https://github.com/Tiifs/chatbubble_variants

```How to install: 
- download the whole pack (click on "CODE" on the top right, then "Download ZIP"
- follow the attached readme file```

There are pictures in the folder, showing you how the chatbubbles would look inside the game once installed.
You have to choose one folder and copy those files over. DO NOT rename the files!

**ElvUI looks zoomed in/ very big when playing on 1440p/ 4k**

This to be expected.
The base profile is made for 1080p since thats the only resolution Robin himself plays on, so the profiles we get from him are made for that scale.

To accomplish the other AddOns lining up with the profile, the scale is set to 0.71 automatically

If you want to get a smaller ElvUI:

1) Import the base profile which will be scaled to 0.71
2) Look at the following addon profiles and where they are in relation to ElvUI:

- BigWigs
- HidingBar
- OmniCD
- Class WeakAuras

3) Change your ElvUI Scale to 0.6
4) Move the AddOns mentioned above to the relative positions on the new scale
5) Profit?

**OR**

adapt to the bigger look, this is the profile thats shipped and you aint getting another

**ICC WA pack for Wrath:**

https://wago.io/sR2538jj7
(same what you get when typing !icc on stream)

AddOns are AddOn files and not ingame profile settings 
Profiles do not automatically change when you update AddOns
You cant auto update profiles
Profile updates overwrite changes made

# How to use WowUp to keep NaowhUI and SharedMedia_Naowh updated

*Prerequisites*
- Latest version of WowUp, Wago or CurseForge does not matter
- Any supported OS (Windows, MacOS, Linux probably too if wowup works there)

Step 1) Install/ Update WowUp from their official website -> [Link](<https://wowup.io/>)
Step 2) Follow the steps described in this picture guide -> [Link](<https://imgur.com/a/7f1gewg>)
Step 3) **Optional** Turn on "Auto Update" by right clicking on the AddOn(s) you want to have automatically updated without checking for updates (-> [Link](<https://imgur.com/a/Q3XgrVV>))

**You only have to enter the links of the github repo once per game version (Retail, Wrath etc.), and for each AddOn seperately**
